1\" AlWHOl\ncooling hod, rufc.\nRexall BORIC ACID Solution\nCleansing, mildly antiseptic. 8 oz.\nBORIC ACID CRYSTALS OR POWDER\nEach 16 ounces, keg 89c 44c\nReg. 47c\nRex-eme MEDICATED CREAM\nFor minor burns, simple skin\nirritations. 12 oz. jar. Reg. 1.23\nRexall PEROXIDE\n3% \u201410 Volume\nCleansing germicide for minor\nwounds, first aid. 8 oz. Reg. 29c\nRexall ANALGESIC BALM\nSoothing ointment, counter-irritant\n1 oz. Reg. 65c\nBIG\nf'emenfousseiechon\n'lne quality P3pers\n1 oo Values\nSAVE!\nCub Scout Banquet\nThursday, Feb. 27, the Mun\nson Cub Scout group held their\nBlue and Gold Banquet in the\nFowlers Mills Church. The La\ndies Aid of the church prepar\ned a most delicious swiss steak\ndinner with all the trimmings.\nApproximately fifty attended\nthe dinner. Reverend Kuehnel\nalso was present. The following\nbadges were awarded this even\ning: Jan Ebert, Lion Badge Ed\nMontgomery, Bobcat and Kit\nHolder, Bear Badge and one\ngold arrow. No special program\nwas planned this time.\nTo You...Our Customer\nOur sincere thanks for your past and\ncontinued patronage. As a further ex\npression of our appreciation to you,\nwe have inaugurated this Special Sale\nof remarkable values. It is always a\nprivilege to serve you.\nSave 24c\nRexall SACCHARIN Tablets\nNon-calcric sweetener. Vi gr 500\u2019s\nReg. 69c\nSave 35c\ni gr. Tablets. 500\u2019s Reg. 75c\nSACCHARIN DROPS in plastic squeeze\nbottle. 25cc. Reg. 65c\nRexall COD LIVER Hit\nSove 48c W\nRexall MILK OF MAGNESIA\nTABLETS\nAntacid, mildly laxative. 36\u2019s.\n30c Value. JF 4.\nSave!\nOs\n9\n^9\nSave 62c\n\u00a3a\nSave 15c w\n3\nSave 33c\nRexall TINCTURE BENZOIN\nCOMPOUND\nUse in steam inhalers. Expectorant\nand mild sedative. 4\nReg.98c\nSave 49c\n'\u00b0C PLAIN ENVEtopiT?\u201d,\n25c RETURN AnnBF\u201eS\u201c'alsi\u00ab.........\nCROMWELL\nMain Street, Chardon\npP CELLO PACKS\nS'\"?\npaper and\n33c\u00ab\nUBKfeS-dT\nSAVE 6c\n2 for .15\n2 for .39\nREXALL DRUG\nAt Home\nMr. Milton Hockman has re\nturned to his home from Lake\nside Hospital following his acci\ndent. Recovery will be slow and\nhe will be confined for several\nmonths. A cheerful card or visit\nwould do wonders to speed his\nrecovery.\nChristine Duncan celebrated\nher seventh birthday on Friday,\nFeb. 28 with her classmates.\nWWW\nHospital Auxiliary\nThe Munson Chapter of the\nGeauga Hospital Auxiliary will\nmeet on Thursday, March 13 at\n8 p.m. at the home of Mrs.\nRichard Vangunten, Bean Rd.\nBy MRS. JAMES RUCH\nMUNSON\u2014 The Annual\nChurch business meeting and\nelection of officers was held at\nthe Church Sunday afternoon.\nThose elected were: Clerk, Rose\nMiller Treas, Paul Herman\nOrganist,* Ruth Parpart Pian\nist, Mary Klatka Choir Direc\ntor, Raymond Osborn Finance\nCom., Paul Herman, Eloni John\nson, Howard Hazen, Arthur\nDorn Flower and Sick Com,\nMillicent Miller, Marion Hazen,\nKatie Yanic, Margaret Hazen,\nBetty Klatka Ladies Aid repre\nsentative, Arlene Car roll Eld\ners, Paul Varney, Elmer Sum\nmer, Mel Johnson, Ray Osborn,\nH. C. Parpart, C. J. Bogaski,\nDeacons, James Ruch, John\nPrice, Art Dorn, Elvin Johnson,\nWillard Herrington, Gale Hazen\nTom Parpart, Phil Kuehnel, and\nRichard Shaffer.\nDeaconesses: May Bogaske,\nHazel Ruch, Ruth Brown, Dor\nothy Johnson, Hazel Hazen,\nMarjorie Osborn, Grace Herman\nDella Varney, Ethel Parpart.\nLois Heinrich, Mary Klatka.\nTrustees: Arlene Carroll, El\nwin Johnson, Howard Hazen,\nPaul Herman and Arthur Dorn.\nS. School Supt. Dorothy John\nson, Secty. Treas.: Fern Wol\no 11 Pianist, Hazel Ruch\nChurch Bulletins, Kay Johnson.\ne were so glad to see Mr.\nand Mrs. Dayri out to church\nSunday. Mr. Dayri hasn\u2019t been\nfeeling very good this winter.\nRuth Parpart was on the sick\nlist with Laringitis the past\nweek.\nThe Young Married Peoples\nSunday School Class party will\nbe held at the home of Mr. and\nMrs. Bill Wolcott, Saturday ev\nening Mrch 15 instead of hhe\n8th.\nChoir practice will be held at\nthe home of Mr. and Mrs. How\nard Hazen Wednesday evening\nfollowed by the Bible Study top\nic to be \u201cThe Good Samaritan\u201d.\nThursday at 12:30 the Ladies\nAid will meet and have a pot\nluck diner after which there will\nBe a White Elephant Sale and\nshort business meeting.\nWe extend our sympathy to\nMrs. Emma Carrolls whose sis\nter, Mrs. Guy Carnegie of Gen\neva died last week.\nWANT-AbS\nBuyer..\nMeets\nSeller..\nthrough\nOur\nClassified\nAd Pages.","height":"28293","width":"21870"}}
